Home Affairs says while very few workers came to work today, it is within their rights according to the settlement. JOHANNESBURG The Home Affairs Department has established that over 90% of its offices are not operating due to insufficient staff members turning up to work this morning.The department says this is due to the settlement agreement with the unions which stipulates that working on Saturday is now voluntary for employees.Home Affairs says while very few workers came to work today, it is within their rights according to the settlement.The department hopes to resolve the matter soon through discussions with unions.The department s David Hlabane says the problem lies in having made working on a Saturday voluntary. Remember that also when we entered into the settlement agreement with the unions on 15 June, part of the agreement was that we re going back to the Bargaining Council for further discussions on the matter. We re hoping that out of those engagements with the unions something may come up. 